    "section_accordion_group_dAJetV": {
      "type": "section-accordion-group",
      "blocks": {
        "heading_QW44cT": {
          "type": "heading",
          "settings": {
            "title": "FAQ"
          }
        },
        "question_LqfH3K": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "default_open": false,
            "title": "Is Polartec Delta actually cooler than a regular moisture-wicking jersey?",
            "content": "<p>Yes. Standard wicking fabrics focus on moving moisture away and drying fast, which can actually short-circuit the body's natural cooling mechanism. Delta takes a different approach: it disperses sweat across the fabric surface to maximize evaporative cooling while reducing the wet, clammy feeling of saturated fabric. The difference is most noticeable in sustained heat and humidity.</p>",
            "show_icon": false,
            "icon_name": "icon-award",
            "icon_size": 20,
            "icon_color": ""
          }
        },
        "question_Lttkci": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "default_open": false,
            "title": "What is Polartec Delta made of?",
            "content": "<p>Delta is a dual-yarn fabric combining Tencel™ lyocell (a cellulose-based hydrophilic fiber) with polyester (a hydrophobic synthetic fiber). The lyocell draws moisture away from the skin. The polyester spreads it for rapid evaporation without absorbing it.</p>",
            "show_icon": false,
            "icon_name": "icon-award",
            "icon_size": 20,
            "icon_color": ""
          }
        },
        "question_pjLqd3": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "default_open": false,
            "title": "What temperatures is the Habanero designed for?",
            "content": "<p>The Habanero is built for hot-weather riding, think 70°F and up, whether that's a San Francisco September or an Austin August. It also works well as a layering piece in milder conditions when you're riding at high intensity.</p>",
            "show_icon": false,
            "icon_name": "icon-award",
            "icon_size": 20,
            "icon_color": ""
          }
        },
        "question_qjmeHW": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "default_open": false,
            "title": "Does the Habanero stick to your skin when you sweat?",
            "content": "<p>No. One of Delta's key design features is reduced wet-cling. The elevated knit structure lifts the fabric off the skin, creating air channels even when you're sweating heavily. You get cooling without the sticky, plastered-on feeling.</p>",
            "show_icon": false,
            "icon_name": "icon-award",
            "icon_size": 20,
            "icon_color": ""
          }
        },
        "question_a3paL4": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "default_open": false,
            "title": "Does Polartec Delta reduce odor?",
            "content": "<p>Yes. The Tencel lyocell fibers in Delta have natural antimicrobial properties that help manage odor from sweat buildup. It won't replace washing, but it extends the fresh window between rides.</p>",
            "show_icon": false,
            "icon_name": "icon-award",
            "icon_size": 20,
            "icon_color": ""
          }
        },
        "question_nPmYKa": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "default_open": false,
            "title": "How should I wash a Polartec Delta jersey?",
            "content": "<p>Cold water, mild detergent, no fabric softener. Lay flat to dry. Skip the dryer, as heat can degrade the fabric's performance over time.</p>",
            "show_icon": false,
            "icon_name": "icon-award",
            "icon_size": 20,
            "icon_color": ""
          }
        },
        "question_xFVAeB": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "default_open": false,
            "title": "What does \"deadstock\" mean?",
            "content": "<p>Deadstock is fabric that was overproduced, abandoned, or never made it to the cutting table. Instead of letting it sit in a warehouse (or worse), we turn it into something new. The catch? We only get one shot. One opportunity. Same Polartec Delta performance, lower environmental impact.</p>",
            "show_icon": false,
            "icon_name": "icon-award",
            "icon_size": 20,
            "icon_color": ""
          }
        },
        "question_XceTAN": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "default_open": false,
            "title": "What is the Special Projects collection?",
            "content": "<p>One of the most sustainable things we can do is use what already exists. Special Projects is our collection of limited-run pieces made from premium deadstock fabrics, cut and sewn in California. Some of our most beloved pieces were born this way. When they're gone, they're gone.</p>",
            "show_icon": false,
            "icon_name": "icon-award",
            "icon_size": 20,
            "icon_color": ""
          }
        }
      },
