        },
        "text_NLYLhd": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>Sweat is your body's radiator. As it evaporates, it carries heat with it. That's evaporative cooling, and it's the most effective way your body sheds excess heat.</p><p>The problem with most performance fabrics: they dry so quickly that evaporation occurs before they can cool you down. You stay dry, but you don't stay cool. Delta disperses moisture instead of eliminating it, so the cooling keeps working.</p>",
            "text_font_size": "body-medium",
            "padding_bottom": 16
          }
        },
